# bad_url_central
# ===============
# Same scoring semantics as bad_url, but intended for a shared/central source.
# Cleanfeed itself performs no network download; an external cron job or timer
# should validate and atomically replace this file.
#
# Exact domain and subdomains:
# (?:[a-z0-9-]+\.)*malware-campaign\.example(?:/|$)
#
# Exact path on a shared legitimate host:
# legitimate-host\.example/drop/campaign-4711(?:[/?#]|$)
#
# Bounded generated hosts:
# click-[a-f0-9]{12}\.tracking-abuse\.example(?:/|$)
#
# Two campaign domains:
# (?:payload-one|payload-two)\.bad-network\.example(?:/|$)
#
# Entries must have published criteria and expiry/review rules. Never add an
# entire URL shortener, cloud provider, public paste service, or top-level
# domain because of one incident.
